The paper discusses Capsule Networks, which are a type of architecture used in Computer Vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Expectation Maximization (EM) algorithm, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of un-equal numbers of EM routing iterations, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses datasets related to facial recognition, traffic sign recognition, and fashion classification, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
